# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback.
# Any non-file, non-/api request falls back to index.html so React Router
# can handle deep links (e.g. /belleair-beach-fl, /tools/pool-volume-calculator).
# The 200 (not 301/302) keeps the URL bar unchanged.
/api/*  /api/:splat  200

# Retired URLs → 301 to a live page. These must come BEFORE the /* catch-all
# (Cloudflare matches top-down, first hit wins); otherwise the catch-all would
# serve the homepage at 200 and the old URL would linger as a soft-404 in Search
# Console. /getstarted was an old "get started" CTA that 404'd (GSC: Not found,
# last crawled Apr 2026) — send it home so Google retires it cleanly. Repoint to
# /signup or /how-it-works/ instead if that's where it should land.
/getstarted   /  301
/getstarted/  /  301

/*      /index.html  200
